name: nytimes
text:
An @nytgraphics analysis of CDC data shows that 345,000 more people than normal have died in the U.S. from March 15 to Nov. 14. That figure, known as excess deaths, is 41% higher than the official coronavirus fatality count.

See more of the analysis here.
